        <p>Yes. If the hosts work at different research institutes, they must each provide a host's statement and confirmation that research facilities can be made available.</p>
    
		

        </div>
    

            
        </div>
    
</section>

            
                <section class="accordion__item">
    <h4 class="accordion__header">
        <button class="js-toggle-accordion accordion__toggle"
                type="button"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="id-12222-content"
                id="id-12222-headline">
            <span class="headline headline--4 f-w-semibold accordion__toggle-label">Will my host institute receive any additional funds for the costs it incurs in connection with my research stay?</span>
            <span class="accordion__toggle-icon"></span>
        </button>
    </h4>
    
        <div class="accordion__content"
            id="id-12222-content"
            aria-labelledby="id-12222-headline">
            
                




        <div class="text text--small">
            
    

    
    
        <p>In general the host institute will receive an allowance for research costs of €800 per month for research in the field of natural sciences and engineering, and €500 for research in the field of humanities or social sciences.</p>
<p>Please see the respective <a href="/en/apply/sponsorship-during-your-stay/sponsorship-during-your-research-stay-in-germany/faq-to-sponsorships-in-germany" class="link link--internal">FAQ of the Department Sponsorship and Network.</a></p>
    
		

        </div>
    

            
        </div>
    
</section>

            
        </div>
    
</section>

                
                    <section class="accordion__item">
    <h3 class="accordion__header">
        <button class="js-toggle-accordion accordion__toggle"
                                          type="button"
                                          aria-expanded="false"
                                          aria-controls="id-12256-content"
                                          id="id-12256-headline">
            <span class="headline headline--3 f-w-semibold accordion__toggle-label">Preparation/Planning</span>
        <span class="accordion__toggle-icon"></span>
    </button>
    </h3>
    
        <div class="accordion__content"
            id="id-12256-content"
            aria-labelledby="id-12256-headline">
            
                <section class="accordion__item">
    <h4 class="accordion__header">
        <button class="js-toggle-accordion accordion__toggle"
                type="button"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="id-12225-content"
                id="id-12225-headline">
            <span class="headline headline--4 f-w-semibold accordion__toggle-label">Are there deadlines for submitting applications?</span>
            <span class="accordion__toggle-icon"></span>
        </button>
    </h4>
    
        <div class="accordion__content"
            id="id-12225-content"
            aria-labelledby="id-12225-headline">
            
                




        <div class="text text--small">
            
    

    
    
        <p>There is no closing date for submitting applications. Applications are processed as part of an ongoing procedure. As soon as we have received your complete application we shall forward it to independent peer reviewers. Their written evaluations will then be presented to the selection committee at the next selection meeting at which a decision will be made.</p>
<p>Please note that you can submit your application only after your host and your expert reviewers have uploaded all necessary documents. The date used to determine whether the applicant meets certain formal requirements, such as career stage limitations and stays in Germany, is the date on which the Humboldt Foundation receives the respective application.</p>
<p>Selection committee meetings take place three times a year, in March, July and November. Applications should be submitted at least four to seven months ahead of the prospective selection meeting.<br> A graphic display of the complete application process can be found above on this page.</p>
    
		

        </div>
    

            
        </div>
    
</section>

            
                <section class="accordion__item">
    <h4 class="accordion__header">
        <button class="js-toggle-accordion accordion__toggle"
                type="button"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="id-12227-content"
                id="id-12227-headline">
            <span class="headline headline--4 f-w-semibold accordion__toggle-label">Can I apply to several Humboldt Foundation fellowship programmes at the same time, or can I apply for a Humboldt Fellowship and the Sofja Kovalevskaja Award at the same time if I fulfil the formal requirements?</span>
            <span class="accordion__toggle-icon"></span>
        </button>
    </h4>
    
        <div class="accordion__content"
            id="id-12227-content"
            aria-labelledby="id-12227-headline">
            
                




        <div class="text text--small">
            
    

    
    
        <p>No, it is not possible to apply to several fellowship programmes or the Sofja Kovalevskaja Award programme concurrently. Should you be rejected by any of them, you may, however, apply to any other programme as long as you fulfil the formal requirements.</p>
    
		

        </div>
    

            
        </div>
    
</section>

            
                <section class="accordion__item">
    <h4 class="accordion__header">
        <button class="js-toggle-accordion accordion__toggle"
                type="button"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="id-12229-content"
                id="id-12229-headline">
